<doc id="1063263" wikidata="Q7617107" url="?curid=1063263" title="Still Me">
<text>Still Me is a 1998 autobiography by American actor Christopher Reeve. The book tells of Reeve&#x27;s experiences of making the &quot;Superman&quot; films and about his horseback riding accident which resulted in his quadriplegia and its effects on his life. The book spent 11 weeks on the &quot;New York Times&quot; Best Seller list in 1998. Reeve won a Grammy Award for Best Spoken Word Album.

